{"slug": "lorehold_spirits", "name": "Lorehold Spirits", "commander": "Quintorius, History Chaser", "colors": "Boros", "pips": ["W", "R"], "archetype": "Spirits / graveyard cycling", "status": "Elite", "bracket": 3, "score": 18, "axes": [{"label": "Core loop", "score": 5}, {"label": "Kill reliability", "score": 5}, {"label": "Durability", "score": 4}, {"label": "Interaction", "score": 4}], "gc": ["Gamble", "Smothering Tithe", "Teferi's Protection"], "clock": {"decap": "T8", "table": "T10", "grid": [5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 12, 14], "decapCurve": [4, 18, 46, 69, 82, 89, 96, 99], "tableCurve": [0, 0, 3, 16, 40, 61, 85, 95], "never": [1, 5], "src": "lab lor_clock_lab @8k"}, "gamePlan": "The engine is graveyard cycling, and the engine is the token engine. Cards entering the graveyard via discard, sacrifice, death, or self-mill set up Quintorius's static; cards leaving the graveyard via recursion fire it. Every recursion event is a Spirit token. Anointed Procession doubles each Spirit. Purphoros pings 2 per Spirit ETB. The deck is designed to feed itself.", "winLine": "Reveillark + Karmic Guide + Goblin Bombardment loop (table)", "finishers": [{"name": "Quintorius Ultimate + Akroma's Will", "tag": "Primary", "note": "Activate Quintorius's \u22124 with 4+ Spirits in play (most turns of the mid-game)."}, {"name": "Purphoros + Procession + Recursion Turn", "tag": "", "note": "With Purphoros and Anointed Procession both in play, every Quintorius static trigger creates 2 Spirits = 4 damage to each opponent from Purphoros."}, {"name": "Moonshaker Cavalry Burst", "tag": "", "note": "Moonshaker Cavalry ETB gives each creature flying + counter."}, {"name": "Boros Charm 4 Damage Mode", "tag": "", "note": "Sometimes the kill is \"Boros Charm 4 damage\" to finish a low-life opponent at instant speed."}, {"name": "Spirit Swarm + Anthem Grindout", "tag": "Backup", "note": "Patchwork Banner, Balefire Liege (+ 3 dmg per RW spell cast), and Tocasia's Welcome (draw) provide a 3\u20134 turn grindout when Quintorius and Moonshaker are both unavailable."}, {"name": "Reveillark / Karmic Guide / Goblin Bombardment Combo", "tag": "", "note": "See Layer 6 above."}], "rulings": [{"name": "Quintorius is a PLANESWALKER, not a creature.", "note": "He survives creature wipes (Wrath, Tragic Arrogance) but dies to combat damage and direct damage \u2014 and cannot be protected by Selfless Spirit / Guardian of Faith."}, {"name": "The static fires once per event", "note": "\u2014 \"one or more cards leave your graveyard\" = ONE Spirit, even when two cards leave at once (Reveillark returning two = 1 token, not 2). Many separate events across a turn is how you stack tokens."}, {"name": "Hofri exiles dying nontoken creatures \u2014 that exile does NOT trigger Quintorius;", "note": "the trigger fires later when the Hofri-token's cards hit the graveyard. Hofri also interferes with the Reveillark loop (Reveillark gets exiled instead of going to the yard) \u2014 remove/sac Hofri first, or use Hofri Spirit tokens as the sac fuel."}, {"name": "Table-check ruling", "note": "whether tokens dying (briefly hitting the yard, then ceasing to exist) triggers the static. Mainstream answer is yes \u2014 meaning dying Hofri Spirits and sacrificed Treasures each fire it. If a judge rules no, several multipliers contract but the engine still runs off real-card recursion."}, {"name": "Goblin Bombardment is an enchantment, not a creature", "note": "\"Sacrifice a creature: 1 damage to any target,\" with no sac cost beyond the creature. It's the loop's free sac outlet; protect it like any combo piece (no in-deck recursion for it)."}], "composition": [{"name": "Game Changers", "count": 3}, {"name": "Token Producers / Spirit Tribal", "count": 7}, {"name": "Token Payoffs", "count": 5}, {"name": "Recursion Engines", "count": 8}, {"name": "Big ETB / Death Trigger Targets", "count": 5}, {"name": "Discard Outlets / Yard Fillers", "count": 5}, {"name": "Sacrifice Outlet", "count": 1}, {"name": "Yard / Li